reviews:
Friendly & helpful staff, clean and newly painted (room 307). Bright and modern decor with elegance.Excellent side view of tower. Loved being so close to the tower, easy access to Metro and dining on Rue Cler, as well as other restaurants.
The room A/C and hotel elevator were excellent.

Just an excellent hotel with an accommodating staff! The location is terrific. We had a small, sitting balcony from which we had a constant view of the Eiffel Tower. Compared to American hotels, the room was a little small, but who will stay in the room in Paris? If we return to Paris, we have already decided this is where we will stay!

My husband and I stayed here for a couple days on our honeymoon. It was such a dream to have our hotel room in such great location and with an amazing view of the Eiffel Tower. The rooms were super clean, the breakfast downstairs was delicious and the concierge was friendly and helpful. I loved staying at La Comtesse--it met high expectations.

Beautiful room, great service, friendly staff and a chance to stay in our favorite neighborhood 7th Arrondissement in Paris!
Special thank you to Hotel Manager Daniel for taking good care of us once again!

Centrally located hotel with a great view of Eiffel Tower. Super friendly and very accommodating staff. I booked this hotel on our last night in Paris which also happens to be my 60th birthday. The hotel upgraded us to a balcony free of charge when they learned that we were there to celebrate. Merci beaucoup! It was a dream come true!!

This hotel was perfect for part of my stay in France! Room with a view of the Eiffel Tower was wonderful. Staff was outstanding and so helpful in finding passes/tickets to sold out places. Loved this hotel!! It will be where I stay every time I go to Paris!

Best boutique hotel in a great location. The service is 4-star along with the accommodations. I highly recommend this hotel if you want to be near the Eiffel Tower and close to everything by taxi or metro.

What a beautiful hotel with a view that cannot be beat! Hotel La Comtesse was located near Ecole Militaire metro station and had a taxi stand across the street from it, making their location easily accessible. There are a lot of great restaurants within walking distance, including the charming Rue Cler. The front desk crew was super helpful and friendly adding to a wonderful stay. I highly recommend Hotel La Comtesse for the great value and experience.

Comfortable bed, the room was very clean and the staff was helpful. We had a great view from the room of the Eiffel Tower. We loved the location. It was close to the metro and walking distance to many restaurants.

Loved this hotel! The personnel, the location, and the room were fantastic! Lovely view of the Eiffel Tower from my room. Delightful Cafe with delicious food. And I can't say enough about the helpful people at the hotel. I can't wait to go back.

The accommodations were wonderful during our entire stay for 3 nights. The room was very comfortable with a direct view of the Eiffel Tower. We had a balcony but were unable to use due to weather. Breakfast every morning was great and the staff was very accommodating throughout our stay. Couldn't have been any better!!

The Hotel is probably 6-7 blocks from the Eiffel Tower. The view of the tower was beautiful at night. There are many restaurants and grocery stores within steps of the property. The employees were very helpful and friendly.

The Hotel staff is Wonderful everyone is so helpful and they all speak French and English. The Hotel is Beautiful and spotless. Very Close to everything. We walked to the Eiffel Tower in less than 10 minutes, The Louve and Notre Dame in 45 minutes. Lots of Cafes very close by. We had a wonderful Trip. This Hotel is perfect for your stay in Paris I would come back and stay here again.

The Concierge staff at Hotel La Comtesse is one of the finest that my wife and I have ever encountered at any hotel anywhere! Emilie and Isabel assisted with a sense of professionalism and can do spirit that is difficult to find these days. They arranged our trips to Versailles and the Eiffel Tower summit, provided directions around town, scheduled taxis and the like with care and immediacy. And they went above-and-beyond to help when I experienced mobile phone problems upon my first day arrival. Can’t rate them highly enough! The breakfast buffet is excellent offering good variety and quality ingredients. Highly recommended! The Hotel is very clean and maid service was timely and top notch. Very conscientious staff! Location is very good - close to the Eiffel Tower, Metro stops, good restaurants. Rooms are well appointed. Bathrooms are modern and full glass encased showers provide good water pressure and all the hot water you want. A 5-star experience for our 5 night stay!

Fine hotel in the 7th. The Director and staff were welcoming and most helpful. Clean, modern bathrooms. Elevator- important as some in our party had mobility issues. While some might think the rooms are small, the size is typical of Paris. The views of the Tower, though not full on, were exceptional. We were a family of 8, ages 77 to 22, and we each were equally pleased with the hotel. Oh, and did I mention Location, Location, Location?
Our best accommodation in the 10 times we’ve been to Paris.

It was a beautiful hotel and the entire staff was extremely polite and very helpful. It was located in an area with several great restaurants. The hotel ordered all our taxi's. A must stay if in Paris.

We visited Paris with our 2 kids (ages 13 and 11) and we loved our stay at Hotel La Comtesse. The location was terrific for visiting all the big spots in Paris - walking distance to most of the sights. The staff was incredibly friendly and the breakfast was great for our kids (who can be picky eaters).

Hotel La Comtesse was probably one of the best parts of our stay in Paris! Receptionist staff were welcoming and helpful. We got a side facing view of the Eiffel Tower and it was amazing to open the little patio and sit out there while enjoying coffee or a glass of champagne! The area where the hotel is located felt clean and safe with plenty of cute cafes within walking distance. Comfortable bed, slept great. Room is overall small but very comfortable and cutely decorated. Would recommend!

My husband and I traveled on holiday to celebrate My Birthday and Our lovely Anniversary. Hotel La Comtesse was BETTER than the pics online. Isabella and Williams we're some of the first staff that we met. They exceeded the mark of hospitality! we felt very comfortable, and the hotel is so clean and friendly. I am so glad that we chose the selection through our vacation package. This hotel is a A+, and a view of the Eiffel tower is so dreamy and amazing. All of the staff was very generous and kind, we truly enjoyed the experience here and I would recommend this to everyone especially if you want to see the Eiffel tower doing your holiday in this beautiful hotel the 7th Arrondissement is truly amazing. Everything is located in walking distance. We walked and took Ubers. The location is overall perfect. Many Thanks to the entire staff at Hotel La Comtesse.

This is Lynne and this was George an my first trip to Paris but it won't be our last. We LOVED our experience there!!! The people were so friendly and the food , oh the food. Most of all our stay at La Comtesse was the BEST. Our room was lovely and our view of the Eiffel Tower magnificient!! Michel at the front desk was SO helpful! Our only regret was that he was off shift when we checked out and we weren't able to thank him for all his assistance to us in person. We WILL stay at La Comtesse aain. Thank you Paris for an unforgetable trip!!!

The rooms are quaint and accommodated all our needs. The bed and pillows were very comfortable and I loved the little extra comfort of the coffee machine. It was a delight to sit outside the balcony and drink an espresso while taking in the beautiful view of the Eiffel Tower. Every staff member from the front desk staff/Concierge to the housekeeping were extremely helpful and professional. Hotel La Comtesse is also located within walking distance to great restaurants and public transportation. I loved our stay and can't wait to return.

This hotel was in a perfect location. Staff was helpful and friendly. View of the Eiffel Tower was incredible. Did not purchase breakfast because we wanted to try local fresh pastries. Incredibly nice young lady checked us in, provided directions to walk to Rue Cler full of amazing local restaurants, bakeries, and shops. She spoke in perfect English, and was so very nice to us, and accommodating. Other hotel staff also provided very easy instructions for nearby Metro to Moulin Rouge where we pre purchased show tickets ahead of time. (Take Metro Line 8 to Concorde, then take Green Line 12 to Pigalle). We arrived safely for the late show that starts at 11 pm for about 4 Euros for both of us. Did not feel unsafe. Had to take a taxi home, as Metro closes at 1 am, for about $16 Euros. Could easily walk over to see “twinkle lights” of the Eiffel on the hours of 10 or 11 pm, for five minute “sparkle show” of the lights.

Stop researching other hotels and hope this one has an open room and book it right now! You will not find a cleaner hotel. We had room 401 which also had a spare twin bed which gave us extra space to store things. Very modern. High quality towels, and towel warmer rack. Our room was right next to the elevator, and we never heard a bit of noise from that. See pics below taken from “open your window and look to the right for Eiffel view”, and pic front of hotel. If we ever go to Paris again, we are staying here!! 10/10!

The junior suite is an extraordinary room, the view to the eiffel tour and the breakfast are absolutely WOW!!!
The location is near to Metro and bus station so if you want to travel from the hotel it is very simple!
Highly recommended!

Excellent hotel nice view close to Effel tower, clean rooms, nice bathroom , great costumer services, I will recommend anybody that goes here or Paris to stays on this hotel, coffee shops , taxis and nice restaurants near by,

The hotel was amazing. Rooms are very efficient (i.e., not large), but comfortable. The front desk was kind and very helpful. We were traveling with our son and his wife, and we were given rooms on the same floor across the hall. The rooms have a view of the Eiffel Tower, but you do have to lean out the window. We enjoyed the view.
My wife loved the automatic nightlight in the bathroom.
The room had all of the amenities you could ask for in a room.
The breakfast is amazing and the view from the restaurant is perfect for a holiday in Paris. Upon leaving, the hotel held our luggage and allowed us to use the bathroom before we left for the airport.
This is a quaint hotel with lots of charm. It was perfect for our time in Paris

We opted for a FRONT FACING view of the Eiffel Tower room, and while the rooms were a “hair” small, we had an absolutely amazing time and view. After we retired for the day, I stood at our open window (even though we had a couple chilly and misty April nights during our stay) and soaked it all up, watching the light show display on the Eiffel Tower each hour it lit up til about midnight. The hotel staff was kind and accommodating, and breakfast on the premises was tasty each morning. Definitely recommend.

From start to finish, the quality and service was 5 star. The hotel provided some special extras to help celebrate my wife's birthday, and it did not go unnoticed!
The staff could not be more helpful, and the breakfast was delicious!
The room was a lovely size, with the most comfortable bed.
The view was top notch! With a glorious view of the eiffel tower.
It's fair to say that the trip was a great success, and the hotel provided the perfect base.
Would love to stay here again, no question!

Small, very clean, and recently renovated hotel with few amenities, but the view from the Eiffel Tower is priceless.

The upgrade for the corner suite room at almost double the price makes you question it first but I don't think the side rooms will do the same justice, so act/ confirm accordingly.
The reception staff is always attentive and communicates well to your needs.

It's in the sophisticated, picturesque 7th arrondissement. So walking distance to the Eiffel Tower. A subway (metro) station is around the corner, in the heart of many cafes and bistros.

We only stayed here for one night but it was the perfect ending to our trip in Paris! Our room had a beautiful view of the Eiffel Tower and my teen daughters basically did a photo shoot all night. 5/5 for sure!

I classify this establishment as a quaint little
Boutique Hotel with charming rooms & spectacular Eiffel Tower Views! Quiet & non smoking - which I love! Furze greeted me by name when I arrive & supplied me with a converter so I was able to charge my phone & use my hair straightener - big Bonus!

Breakfast was “good” - maybe it’s best to not make so many pastries at once so they stay fresh as there were a bunch that had been sitting out for quite some time & gotten cold. A toaster would’ve been great but I didnt see one. The BEST orange juice I’ve ever had!!!!

I picked this hotel for the Eiffel Tower view & it did not disappoint! It met all my expectations!

We had a wonderful stay at Hotel Comtesse to celebrate my husband's birthday. We upgraded to a balcony room with a view of the Tower for one evening and moved to a regular Prestige room the other evenings. Highly recommend upgrading at least for one night for the view! The other rooms have a view if you peer out the side. The staff was friendly and the hotel is very cozy.

Excellent hotel super clean amazing staff Especially Furis who upgraded my room to one with a balcony with a direct Eiffel Tower view ! The only complaint I would have is the rooms are way too small although bigger than slot of rooms for Paris still small . Also the downstairs restaurant closes after lunch so , no food or bar unless you go out or Uber in .

Excellent service, great rooms. Incredible view. Was lucky that there was a balcony available when we arrived and only had to pay a small upcharge for each night. Great deal on breakfast if you decide to have it downstairs or sent to your room.

Me and my boyfriend really enjoyed our stay at this hotel for his birthday. The room was quite small but I guess that's to be expected in Paris. The bathroom and shower were great. Free breakfast included with stay was delicious and the staff were all super friendly and accommodating. Added bonus was seeing the Eiffel Tower from our room window. I would definitely stay here again.

The Staff was really friendly and helpful. The beds were comfortable, rooms clean and up to date. The Cafe associated in the Hotel was excellent and that staff was also very friendly. Great location with dining, shopping, Pharmacy, Laundry Mat and ATM's close by. Eiffel Tower a 15–20-minute walk from the Hotel. (Was just me and my Daughter)

Clean, comfy room. Beautiful accommodations. Beautiful view! Would stay here again, but skip the breakfast not worth the money. The staff are very nice and friendly and we’re able to give us everything we needed.

we were very satisfiedthe gentleman at the reception was very helpful and very polite.. we were very pleased, thank you very much for everything.hotel rooms were nice and simple.. it was clean thank you very much

Great hotel near Eiffel Tower! Good restaurants nearby, tons of Paris highlights close by with walking distance. Hotel staff is very nice and helpful, great breakfast and lookouts of the tower from the hotel! Overall great place to stay while in Paris!

I wanted say a big thank you 🙏🏻

My staying in the 605 for 2 nights with my wife has been amazing.

Everything was perfect, the room, the breakfast, the kindness of the staff, the decoration and the bottle of champagne at the arrival.

The room with the balcony that as been offered with such as amazing view..

I will definitely choose hotel la comtesse again ✨🙏🏻

Staff was very friendly and helpful. Location was perfect, minutes away from the Eiffel Tower, metro station and bus stop. Plenty to do in the surrounding neighborhood. Great hotel for first time visitors. Would absolutely recommend

Best view hands down. We got so many amazing pictures from the cute balcony. Highly recommend this place to anyone wanting an Eiffel tower view. The staff was also extremely nice and were happy to give us advice on where to go when we got there!

Booked because of the view to Eiffel Tower. Very clean and would definitely stop again.
Staff friendly and accommodating. Lovely stay good location for the Eiffel Tower.
The room was well equipped with hairdryer, iron and ironing board. Warm drink facilities. And the bathroom was well equipped with shower gel, shampoo and body lotion ect.

Nice hotel, friendly and respectful staffs, you get a nice view of the Eiffel Tower. The hotel is close to champs elysee and 10 mins walk to Eiffel Tower. Breakfast was excellent will stay there again next time I come to Paris.

Great staff, great location. Always ready to provide help and advice on getting around. Accommodating on all matters related to the stay. Clean and comfortable. Near taxi stand and metro. Reasonable prices.

Loved this hotel - simple - friendly - superb location. We stayed in February and walked everywhere. 10 minutes to the Eiffel Tower and so much to do and see around here. Really clean and breakfasts were lovely

We had a wonderful time at Hotel La Contessa - The staff took care of every single detail from flowers to a private driver. The view from our room was stunning. We will definitely come back to stay in this hotel again.

We absolutely loved this hotel. It was perfectly placed near, but not too close to the Eiffel Tower - and it was close to the metro. The staff were amazing, very helpful and kind. The little restaurant has a nice breakfast and lovely offerings. The hotel has an elevator, and the room was a good size with a nice bathroom. I highly recommend this location.

Nice view of the Eiffel tower when you lean out of the balcony.
Small room but soundproofed and had everything we needed but could have done with plug sockets near the bed.
Would not bother using the Gym room as was tiny with only two different machines.
Also wanted us to pay for a teabag when we wanted an extra one but didn’t replenish each day.
Overall a nice stay but have stayed in better hotels in Paris with value for money

Such a beautiful boutique hotel. We absolutely loved our stay - our room was impeccably clean, the concierge and front desk was friendly and helpful, and the views of the Eiffel Tower from our window weren’t bad either. The location was absolutely perfect for us - so close to the 8 Metro and 92 bus stop, and less than a 15 min walk to the Eiffel Tower. Also, a 5 min walk to Rue Cler Market street with a ton of restaurants and boulangeries which we would recommend stopping by and exploring. Overall, we would highly recommend La Comtesse and plan to come back as soon as possible!!

We paid an extremely high rate for a side view of the tower in a 4 star hotel. The side view means you open both sides of the window,( freezing, raining or hot outside) Stick your head out of the window, turn and lean to see it. It was a joke but I crossed it off as a lesson learned but then at check in they told us the restaurant was closed and no room service because the one employee called in. The next day, the restaurant was again closed to private booking and no room service... no bar, nothing! The hotel refused to give us a partial refund even tho it was only a 2 star. Reception was constantly on personal phone calls and never able to assist during our stay. Tip: Book a company chain hotel that stands behind the services and property. Never again here tho

Thank you to all team ot Hotel La Comtesse. The experience was amazing and memorable. We had a room with Eiffel Tower side view and balcony. It was absolutely amazing, rooms were clean and very warm. We will come back again for sure.

We were looking for the perfect Eiffel Tower room view and we found it! The room was lovely, spacious bathroom and bedroom. Water and chocolates complimentary. Staff was pleasant and helpful. Perfect for pictures from the balcony. Highly recommend!

I absolutely adored staying at the salon-styled Hotel La Comtesse near the Eiffel Tower in the 7th Arondissement of Paris.
The aesthetic is gorgeous, the staff are lovely and the breakfast is magnifique!
The amenities also include a hammam/Turkish bath which is a must for any visitor who want to spa on their vacation.

We greatly enjoyed our stay at La Comtesse. It has wonderful views of the Eiffel Tower, very clean rooms with modern decor, comfortable beds, and very well-stocked mini bars. The staff were excellent and went above and beyond to make us feel welcomed and taken care of. We were exhausted after 24 hours of traveling to get to Paris and they were very generous and accommodating with allowing us to check-in early so we could get some much needed rest. I’m so sorry I forget the name of the one receptionist (the one who did Erasmus in the US), but he made some excellent bar and restaurant recommendations to us and really went out of his way to let us know what was in the neighborhood. Breakfast in their cafe is delicious and offers many options; I would definitely recommend taking advantage of it. We travel a lot and I can say that this is the best boutique hotel that we’ve ever stayed in. We would definitely stay here again!

Front desk concierge Jean-Michel was very kind, and polite and made my stay pleasant. He speaks English well and has great recommendations on what to do and where to find things. He was the best. The breakfast hours in the dining area were long enough for a jet-lagged tourist.

This was a great hotel for our visit to Paris. It’s location is convenient to everything. You can see the Eiffel Tower from the hotel rooms and walk to it in a few minutes. But keep in mind the only hotel rooms that have a straight on view of the Eiffel Tower are the upgraded rooms or else you have to open your windows and look either left or right to see the beautiful Eiffel Tower. They are still great views. The other rooms also look a little bit bigger which is important because the room I had was a bit snug for two people and our luggage. Next time I will definitely upgrade to one of those superior rooms. Location is also central to many good restaurants. The staff was excellent and set up taxis and other requests that we asked for. Great location and really nice experience. Definitely a very good choice for your stay in Paris.

Beautiful hotel in a superb location. You can see the Eiffel Tower from the hotel. Metro station is very close by as are many restaurants and a supermarket too! The staff are very helpful and polite, the rooms are clean and comfortable, the breakfast was great. Would definitely stay again. Thank you!

The hotel staffs are very Friendly. The room is very clean and can see Eiffel towet. The location is strategic with many nice restaurants and walking shortly to Eiffel Tower. Metro is also walking distance

Perfect location and view of Eiffel Tower. Great places to eat around hotel, conveniently close to metro station and super market. Some other great perks of location, bank, currency exchange, pharmacy, laundry mat if needed. Staff made our stay comfortable, very nice staff, and aimed to please. I would definitely stay here again.

Hotel seems ok customer service is terrible only one person on reception, seems really stressed durinhcheck in argumentative and unnecessary rude made me feel very upset before I even started my stay. The lady on reception name was Emile.

This is by far the best Hotel to stay at in Paris. The rooms were very clean and comfortable. The staff were courteous and considerate. We were there for the Christmas holiday and watched the staff work tirelessly to ensure our stay was perfect. The view from our room included the Eiffel Tower. The actually Hotel manager was handling several positions as he had given his crew time off for the holiday. As a business owner I understood his sacrifice. At all time he was professional and pleasant to talk with. The included breakfast was also very delicious. This is a top notch Hotel and this is where we will stay on each trip to Paris

The best hotel in Paris . Friendly staff, clean rooms and a magical view of the Eiffel Tower. Very good breakfast , lunch and wine . The hotel is located near a metro and bus station . Also near in the Eiffel Tower (5 minutes walk)

very nice view on the eiffel, nice staff wich were really helpfull. service was literally perfect, got a free upgrade to a room with a balcony with a perfect view of the city on the 5th floor. the room was very clean, modern tv, very new bathroom wich looked amazing with a bathtub and most importantly the beds were really comfortable.

A beautiful small hotel that was welcoming and had the most perfect view of the Eiffel tower. The location of the hotel was also great for walking to anywhere you need to go. We will absolutely be back.

Very friendly staff, great breakfast (loved a small pitcher of fresh orange juice on every table), excellent view from the window and location (right between Champ de Mars and Invalides), planning to return here next year to enjoy again this lovely hotel

Great location, very friendly staff, very comfortable bed with an awesome view of the Eiffel Tower!! We had a great balcony where we sat and looked at the tower!

We visited in December of 2022 and we loved it!

Lovely hotel with friendly and helpful staff! Beautifully decorated for Christmas! Great location close to the Eiffel Tower, Rue Cler and the Military Museum. Metro, money exchange, launderette and many restaurants close by.

Great view of Eiffel Tower from our balcony. Had room turnover and fresh towels every day. The rooms are tiny but we didn’t spend much time there anyways. Great central location and could walk to Eiffel Tower easily within 10 min. Shower got HOT! Metro stop right around corner. Would stay again and recommend! Had the marquis room with balcony upgrade.

This was our first Holiday visit to Paris so we don’t have a lot to compare to. I will say that the stay was very enjoyable! The staff was amazing and the location was fantastic! The bed was very comfortable and the room was very quiet at night. We also enjoyed the cafe. The breakfast was great and the service was very good! We will come back in the spring time for sure!

Great hotel with a fantastic view of Eiffel Tower. No complaints about the room/services. Location is convenient- close to metro and lots of cafes around. You could also walk to a lot of tourist spots from this location.
Nice and clean place, bed was comfortable, staff attentive. The best part is the location which is within walking distance from the Eiffel tower, multiple activities, souvenirs shops and restaurants.

Super friendly staff members! Safe, clean, beautiful and quiet area with metro station close by, extremely nice and convenient! Rooms are lovely, cozy and comfy with a stunning view of the Eiffel Tower at night time! The breakfast was amazing too!

The hotel is a very warm, relaxing and sweet place to go back to after a busy day of activities and visits in the city. Will surely come back when we visit Paris again next time!

The room was great, staff was very nice, room was cleaned daily and the view to the Eifel tower was great.
the hotel is very close to the subway which takes you everywhere you want to go.
we definitely recommend

The hotel is located in a great neighborhood, walking distance to some really fine boulangeries and patisseries, chocolatiers, restaurants and fine dining establishments. Metro station is right up the street, 1 min walk, from the hotel. Easy check-in process. The room and amenities were excellent. Mattress was super comfortable, and the bathroom spacious and comes with a towel warmer. The most spectacular thing about the room is that the Eiffel Tour is within view from the window. Such a spectacular site both day and night. Finally, checkout was easy, and the staff were kind enough to arrange for a large taxi to accommodate us and our big suitcases.

The perfect Paris experience: sitting on a balcony, sipping a latte, while the Eiffel Tower sparkles in the night.

What a great hotel. I don’t usually spend a lot on hotels, but we went a bit over budget for this hotel, and wow! So worth it. The views of the Eiffel Tower were amazing even if they weren’t straight on. We were fortunate enough to get a balcony room. Even in the cold December evening, it was amazing sitting out there to stare at the tower.

- We stayed in the Triple Duchess room. It was spacious and enough room to open all 3 luggages
- Hotel location is good, near bus stop and metro station. Taxi stand opposite hotel too. Supermarkets and eateries nearby too - Hotel is clean and safe which is very important factor for travelers
- though it’s only a small boutique hotel, breakfast spread is sufficient, with fruits provided too. We enjoyed eating the piping hot ham and mushroom omelette every morning
- most of all, it has a breathtaking view of the Eiffel Tower at the balcony! Even in the restaurant, there are some tables where you can see the Tower.
Only negative is the room lighting is abit too dim. May be can place some hooks near door entrance to hang our coats or jackets. Nevertheless we had a great stay!

Beautiful view of the Effiel tower! Great location for public transit and attractions. A close walk to the Effiel tower, great shops, restaurants, and cafes near by. I would highly recommend. Staff is very friendly and accommodating.

We wanted to stay in a hotel close the city centre and this was the perfect location. Welcoming, friendly and helpful staff, clean hotel room with daily housekeeping and Wifi Access. Our room had a side view of the Eiffel Tower and within a 5/10 minute walk you are right next to it! It has a pharmacy and a few lovely restaurants right outside and Ecole Militare metro station round the corner. I had the small €10 breakfast which included coffee or tea, 3 mini pastries and orange juice but there was a more expensive option which offered a range of egg and other hot food. If we come back to Paris we will definitely be staying here again, I would recommend to everyone.

The view was great, and the lady at the front desk was so kind and accommodating. We enjoyed her tremendously! They let us drop bags early, and leave a few minutes late because our flight was later in the day. Worth the money!

Hotel La Comtesse is the best hotel I’ve ever stayed at! The location was perfect and the staff were so welcoming and helped make my birthday special. Our room was beautiful and had the most breathtaking view of the Tour Eiffel. We preordered seasonal flowers for my birthday and they were a stunning bouquet of pink roses. We also ordered breakfast and it was very very delicious. Everything about this hotel is perfect and I will be returning very soon!

A perfect hotel to have perfect parisian experience ! the hotel is small and intimate as are the rooms.We had an amazing view of the eiffel tower !
The concierge and breakfast are amazing . The location is incredible walking distance to everywhere. we will return

We stayed at La Comtesse at the weekend. I am not a huge fan of hotels as find most noisy and impersonal, well not this one! The staff were fantastic from the moment we arrived. Our room was beautiful with a balcony and a superb view of the Eiffel Tower. It’s close to some great cafes and restaurants and a short walk to the Eiffel Tower and boats. Breakfast was extremely good and I would highly recommend.
I wouldnt stay anywhere else in Paris.

They were very gracious and accommodating with our stay in Paris! They were very welcoming upon our arrival and helpful throughout the entire visit. I got the room I wanted, with the view of the Eiffel Tower, couldn't have been any more perfect. I would definitely choose Hôtel La Comtesse on my next trip in Paris!!

My partner and I stayed here for a long weekend getaway. Everyone at the hotel was friendly, welcoming, and accommodating. The rooms were small but were clean, had the essentials with great views! The location is absolutely perfect--you can walk to the Eiffel tower, and lots of cute cafes and shops along the way.

Great hotel to stay at. View of Eiffel tower was incredible, breakfast each morning was great. Noise was a non factor the week i was there as i hardly noticed i had neighbors for the week. Staff was helpful and hotel is located feet from multiple sidewalk cafes and the metro. Room had very nice espresso machine i used each morning.

What a beautiful hotel. Great ambiance, friendly and helpful staff. Great location with views of the Eiffel Tower. Walking distance to great restaurants and tourist attractions. Would highly recommend

The room was wonderful. The Front Desk clerks that I have interacted with were excellent. The Cleaning staff did a wonderful job with my room. The best part was the location of the Hotel, with a direct view of the Eiffel Tower. I enjoyed my stay so much.

The location, views, and staff were all exceptional. Emilie went above and beyond for us before and during our stay. The suite with the Eiffel Tower view was stunning. The shower was super comfortable and hot. Lots of cafes, restaurants, shops and a pharmacy were all walkable.

The room was comfortable and had everything we needed for a week's stay in Paris. Our view was fantastic and we checked on the Eiffel Tower several times. Loved the coffee although our machine was sensitive and took a few tries to get to work each time. The staff was attentive and polite and arranged for our transfer back to the airport. The central location in the 7th arron can't be beat. Close to metro, laundry, pharmacy. Would book again in a heartbeat!

They were very accommodating, they offered early check in as well as provided luggage locker till our check in time and helped us get a car service from the airport. It was all smooth process. The side view room was truly perfect, they were in a wonderful location. Walking distance from the tower, restaurants and museums. I would make this my go to hotel when visiting Paris.

Very cute boutique hotel that has all the amenities and is spacious for a european hotel. The front desk is very helpful and friendly. Location is good and close to some cute bakeries, bars and metro.

We truly enjoyed our time. The wait staff made it extra special. Rooms were very small, but they usually are in Paris. Right? The location is extremely close to the Eiffel Tower. There are several great restaurants near by!

We absolutely loved our stay here! My wife and I came here on our honeymoon. The service was incredible and the view from the room is magical! The rooms were clean and well equipped, location was easy to get around, and breakfast was very tasty. Highly recommend staying here!

The hotel was very clean and centrally located near the Eiffel Tower. The bed was comfortable and shower was awesome! Lots of great sightseeing, patisseries, and restaurants within walking distance. I enjoyed my time there and would highly recommend it to others.

Great hotel, very clean, awesome view and not very expensive considering the prices at other hotels. Friendly staff too. I like that I got an email before my arrival date confirming my reservation and I could request add ons such as chocolates and flowers.. for a price of course. I didn’t request anything but it was nice to have.
Downside: check in was a bit awkward and the gentlemen took my payment right away which is a bit odd to me cause it’s usually done at check out. Also he didn’t really go through what to expect at the hotel, or that sort of thing.
The next lady was way better and provided more information that was helpful.
Breakfast didn’t look super interesting and I didn’t like that it was self serve.
However I would stay here again as it was a very lovely hotel and the location is great!
I had the duchess room with balcony and it was a very decent size.

My daughter brought me to Paris to fulfill my lifelong dream! Hotel La Comtesse was perfect. The rooms were comfortable and a perfect place for rest between outings! The staff was friendly and helpful!

Excellent location. Close to restaurants. Short walk to Eiffel Tower and Seine River. Gorgeous spacious room with view of the Eiffel Tower. Comfortable bed. Wonderful breakfast with lots of options. Friendly staff. Would definitely stay here again.

We had a lovely birthday trip to Paris, Hotel was amazing with amazing views. the staff were friendly and the room looked amazing. it was near all local shops and the views were 360. will defo come back and stay.

The staff were wonderful, especially Michael! The room was clean & comfortable, but small. We had an amazing view of the Eiffel Tower from room 203. The only negative was that the hotel is either Heat or Air as a whole, meaning if it is heat than every room room in the hotel has heat, so you can not have Air in just your room.

Great location. Staff was friendly and helpful. Nice view of tower. Closely located to public transportation. Room was clean and quiet, even on busy corner. Only downsides were not much room in fridge and shower drain was clogged and backed up easily.
